so this weekend really kicked ass
so much happened and it was all so very great
first friday i came home and then and went to zia
cause simplfy was playing and it was so outstanding
then we talked to rob and told him we had to go 
so we left to the marquee theater 
and got there just in time to see authority zero
oh man and they put on a amazing show 
i could cry cause or how great it was
just everything was so wonderful about it 
the crowd, the friends, and especially the band
so then pepper came on and it was the worst 
i will forever long dislike pepper 
it was a great night and wont ever forget it 


Then saturday came and i went to a unity walk with my two sisters
it was very cool lots of people were there
and i saw some pretty awesome talents that blew me away
came home after that and slept hahaha
i woke up and got ready to go to another show
we went to the marquee theater again
and we got the last parking spot in the place 
we went inside and waited for straylight run to come 
and sang our little hearts out 
it was so beautiful
i saw brad and didnt really think it was him so i told kally 
and come to find out it was him
so we waved to him and his girlfriend
it was about 8:54 and simplfy was going to come on at 9:10 
so i asked if we could stay for just one more song
and when i asked that they announced that it was there last song
so we were able to see all of straylight run
it was a great show
so then right when they hit the last note 
we walked very fast out of that place
and right when we got out of the marquee we ran all the way to the car 
which was kinda far 
so we shoved each other in the car
and sped almost the whole way 
and those damn stop lights took forever
so i had to go push the button thing so we should go
then we finally got to the sets and it was 9:15 
and we were so happy that we made it and then we just froze
when we saw the freakin line it was so long
we almost cryed
we were hoping that they would be behind schedule but no for one day they 
were right on time
we stood in line for about 10,15 minutes 
it was horrible hearing simplfy from outside and not being able to be inside with them
FINALLY we got in and ran to the front not caring whos way we would be blocking
and was able to see them for about 3 songs or so 
it was one of simplfys best show 
everyone had so much energy 
then when they finished their set we were kicked out 
so we hung out outside and talked to a few of the fellows in the band
then we went to eat at ihop 
and saw triston and jason and scott 
funny guys 
then went to kallys and told scary stories and played with candles 

the best part about this weekend was the people that i was with
i have the best friends in the world 
and i wouldnt give them up for the world

thanks for reading

and all you have are all of those great memories that you can still laugh to

and you might feel replaced but you try to keep that far from your mind 
cause you know or hope they wouldnt do that 
but then it gets so silent that you just know its going to happen
and that makes you sad
but really there is only so much you can do and keep tying and trying
then you will get to a point where you almost want it to stop and give up 
and then you fell lost and not like yourself
